  • Method Details

    • validate

      boolean validate​(T t)
      Checks if the specified value is valid.

      This method is oftentimes executed inside of a loop. It is therefore recommended to avoid the following when using this method (when possible):
      1. Lengthy operations
      2. CPU intensive operations
      3. The modification of any external values based on this method's result
      Parameters:
      t - The object that is being validated.
      Returns:
      True if the specified object is valid based on this Validatable, false otherwise.

    • postValidation

      default boolean postValidation​(T t, boolean wasValid)
      Executes any post-validation cleanup operations.

      This method does not always run directly after the validate(T) method is finished executing. However, it can be assumed that this method will be executed on a single Validatable object after an operation is completed.

      The default implementation of this method always returns true.

      Parameters:
      t - The object that was validated by validate(T).
      wasValid - True if the result returned by validate(T) was true, false otherwise.
      Returns:
      True if the post validation process was successful, false otherwise.

      True by default.
